{"talk":{"id":11226,"name":"Dustin Schroeder: How we look kilometers below the Antarctic ice sheet","description":"Antarctica is a vast and dynamic place, but radar technologies -- from World War II-era film to state-of-the-art miniaturized sensors -- are enabling scientists to observe and understand changes beneath the continent's ice in unprecedented detail. Join radio glaciologist Dustin Schroeder on a flight high above Antarctica and see how ice-penetrating radar is helping us learn about future sea level rise -- and what the melting ice will mean for us all.","slug":"dustin_schroeder_how_we_look_kilometers_below_the_antarctic_ice_sheet","recorded_at":"2017-04-23 00:00:00","published_at":"2018-03-01 15:59:53","updated_at":"2021-04-09 19:47:09","viewed_count":967811,"emailed_count":0,"event":{"id":233,"name":"TEDxStanford"},"images":[{"image":{"size":"113x85","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/8db5be32c0282d150a1905c6f0c57e01f365f640_113x85.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"240x180","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/8db5be32c0282d150a1905c6f0c57e01f365f640_240x180.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"615x461","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/8db5be32c0282d150a1905c6f0c57e01f365f640_615x461.jpg"}},{"image":{"size":"2400x1800","url":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/8db5be32c0282d150a1905c6f0c57e01f365f640_2400x1800.jpg"}}],"image_16x9":"https:\/\/pe.tedcdn.com\/images\/ted\/b643c24b228e49e445aa14c17c10e38bed229b05_2880x1620.jpg","media":{"internal":{"64k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/DustinSchroeder_2017X-64k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":5539119,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"180k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/DustinSchroeder_2017X-180k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes":15329810,"mime_type":"video\/mp4"},"320k":{"uri":"https:\/\/download.ted.com\/talks\/DustinSchroeder_2017X-320k.mp4?apikey=c692baa7dafbf74e4fbde1ac88b44cafc96cfe7a","filesize_bytes"